Gradle command to rune application


To run an Android application using Gradle, you typically use the installDebug or install task, depending on your build configuration. Here are the basic commands:

./gradlew installDebug
./gradlew installRelease
./gradlew installRelease

To see a list of all available build tasks for your project, execute tasks:
gradlew tasks

Build an app bundle with Gradle
./gradlew :base:bundleDebug
